During the Ash-and-Iron Decades, Midgaard magistrates issued sealed warrants condemning debtors and unregistered persons to labor service.
The Violet Compact's registry processed these people as "arcane material," stripping civic identity.
The Spirebound Conclave received them for experimentation: crystal-binding, sentinel forging, spirit imprinting.

Midgaard's trade ledger has one surviving line: payment of "forty iron bars and six condemned debtors" to "the mountain academy."
Kowloon's Black Ledger, if it exists, holds corresponding entries from the delta settlements.
The Conclave's experiment records survive in the Sunken Sanctum's sealed vaults.

The Violet Eclipse Cathedral processed transit warrants and held condemned persons in quarantine.
When it withdrew into eclipse, it took transit ledgers that Midgaard's Reckoning Faction has sought for generations.

Both Midgaard and Kowloon have Reckoning factions seeking exposure and Continuity factions seeking burial.
Neither can prosecute the other without opening its own archive.
Kiess's founding charter explicitly forbids sealed-warrant governance as a direct response to Evermeet's participation.
